metadata.title: De Havilland Canada Dash 8
aws::graph::propositions: De Havilland Canada Dash 8 Q400 Variants
All Q400s include the Active Noise and Vibration Suppression (ANVS) system.
Q400NextGen is a version of the Q400 with updated cabins.
An Extra Capacity variant of the Q400 was introduced in 2013.
The Extra Capacity variant is capable of carrying a maximum of 86 passengers.
The Extra Capacity variant was updated in 2016 with more closely spaced seats.
The updated Extra Capacity variant can carry up to 90 passengers.
The first 90-seat Q400 aircraft was delivered to SpiceJet in September 2018.
SpiceJet was the launch customer for the 90-seat Q400 aircraft.
Over sixteen Q400 aircraft have been adapted to the aerial firefighting role as an airtanker.
The Q400AT is also called the Dash 8-400AT (airtanker only).
The Q400AT is also called the Dash 8-400MRE (multi-role airtanker).

text:
All Q400s include the ANVS (Active Noise and Vibration Suppression) system.
Q400NextGen
Version of the Q400 with updated cabins, lighting, windows, overhead bins, landing gear, as well as reduced fuel and maintenance costs.
In 2013, an Extra Capacity variant was introduced, capable of carrying a maximum of 86 passengers. The Extra Capacity variant was updated in 2016 with more closely spaced seats to carry up to 90 passengers. The first 90-seat aircraft was delivered to launch customer SpiceJet in September 2018.
Q400-MR (now Q400AT)
Over sixteen Q400 aircraft have been adapted to the aerial firefighting role as an airtanker. This aircraft is also called the Dash 8-400AT (airtanker only) or Dash 8-400MRE (multi-role airtanker).
